<h1>How to Cite MantaMatcher and Collaborative Data</h1>

<p>Even if a collaborative link has been made between users, MantaMatcher requests you to contact the data provider(s) for use of any and all data shared in a collaboration if it is to be used in any publication, product, or commercial application.</p>

<p>By using MantaMatcher the user agrees to the following:
	<ol>
		<li>Not to use data contained in MantaMatcher in any publication, product, or commercial application without prior written consent of the original data provider.</li>
		<li>To cite both the data provider(s) and Mantamatcher appropriately after approval of use is obtained.
			<ul>
				<li>Collaborative datasets should list all data contributors in descending order of quantity of encounters contributed. The year should be listed as the year when the dataset was pooled and downloaded.</li>
				<li>Example citation for a dataset:
					<ul>
						<li>A. Marshall, J. Holmberg, A. Marine-Biologist, C. Researcher, O. Cean.  (2016). Collaborative dataset from: mantamatcher.org. Consolidated and downloaded: June 15, 2016.</li>
					
					</ul>
				
				</li>
				<li>General citation for MantaMatcher:
					<ul>
						<li>A. Marshall and J. Holmberg. 2011. MantaMatcher: a cloud-based photo-identification analysis tools for manta research. Accessible at: https://www.mantamatcher.org </li>
					
					</ul>
				
				</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>To forward the citation of any publication / report that made use of the data / tools provided by MantaMatcher for inclusion in our list of references. Submit here: info@wildme.org</li>
		<li>Not to hold MantaMatcher or the original data providers liable for errors in the data. While we have made every effort to ensure the quality of the database, we cannot guarantee the accuracy of these datasets.</li>
	</ol>
</p>	

